newsitem.title: VENEZUELA: Venezuelan M-2 falls 0.25 percent in week.
newsitem.headline: Venezuelan M-2 falls 0.25 percent in week.

text.p: Venezuelan money supply, as measured by the monetary aggregate M-2, fell 0.25 percent to 4.204 trillion bolivars in the week to Sept 27, the central bank said.
At the beginning of 1996, M-2 was 3.530 trillion bolivars.
